div.p:
Object. 21.

   When I was told how you challenged any Scholler to ſhew where any Nation enjoyed the Goſpell for an hundred yeares together;
 it put me in mind of a witty Gentlemans anſwer to one that asked, what if a Papiſt ſhould aske a Presbyterian where his Religion was 200. year ago? he might anſwer I know no more where it was two hundred year ago, then where it will be two hundred year hence: but (not to allow my ſelf even a ſober mirth on ſo ſad an occaſion) this puts me in mind of Biſhop Halls ſolemne offer: That if any man living can ſhew any one lay Presbyter that ever was in the World till Farell and Viret, or any Presbyterian Diſcipline till Mr. Calvin ſet one up,—let me (ſaith he) forfeit my reputation to ſhame, and my life to juſtice.—
